        {
            "id": "4fff6037c02f4742b80f4",
            "questionText": "A bowling ball, modeled as a sphere with a mass $!$M = 7\\,\\text{kg}$!$ and a radius $!$R = 0.1\\,\\text{m}$!$, rolls without slipping down a bowling lane. Its center of mass travels at a linear velocity of $!$v = 4\\,\\text{m/s}$!$. Determine the magnitude of its angular momentum.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "a7bbd4a773d9487db40bd",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by recalling the expression for the moment of inertia of a sphere. Please choose the correct formula for the moment of inertia of a solid sphere.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "f6586b7d-c0fe-4287-91e9-f20de7e236bd"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I = \\frac{1}{2} M R^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I = \\frac{2}{5} M R^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I = M R^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "9747aded9970469bad7a2",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, since the ball rolls without slipping, there is a specific relationship between its linear speed and its angular speed. Identify the correct relation connecting $!$v$!$ and $!$\\omega$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "daaa4850-76fd-458c-99ae-480cec59b41f"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\omega = v \\cdot R$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\omega = \\frac{v}{R}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\omega = \\frac{R}{v}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "c04b590a7e9a496299a31",
                    "stepText": "Now, using the correct moment of inertia formula and the given values $!$M = 7\\,\\text{kg}$!$ and $!$R = 0.1\\,\\text{m}$!$, calculate the moment of inertia of the bowling ball. Enter the numerical value.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.028"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "kg\u00b7m\u00b2",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "f6586b7d-c0fe-4287-91e9-f20de7e236bd"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "ffaf145223a74a34bc7e7",
                    "stepText": "Excellent. Next, calculate the angular velocity using the relation from the previous step with the given linear speed $!$v = 4\\,\\text{m/s}$!$ and $!$R = 0.1\\,\\text{m}$!$. Compute its value.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "40"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "rad/s",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "daaa4850-76fd-458c-99ae-480cec59b41f"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "b9d78d50cbe9476e8c17c",
                    "stepText": "Finally, now that you have both the moment of inertia and the angular velocity, use them to determine the angular momentum of the bowling ball. Compute the final numerical value.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "1.12"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "kg\u00b7m\u00b2/s",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "2b9428ca-8d6d-4190-afd1-29f6d9298536",
                        "f6586b7d-c0fe-4287-91e9-f20de7e236bd"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                }
            ]
